Sentencas: Better interfacial bonding with fewer dislocations is observed between in-situ TiC and hastelloy than that between ex-situ TiC and hastelloy, which slows down the diffusion rate of Ti and O during oxidation process.
Titulo: Interfacial effect on oxidation resistance of TiC/hastelloy composites applied for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnects

Sentencas: Mass gain (800 degrees C/100 h) of in-situ TiC/hastelloy composites is 2.60 mg cm(-2) with oxidation rate 6.84 x 10(-8) g(2) cm(-4) h(-1), much lower than 4.17 mg cm(-2) with oxidation rate of 1.75 x 10(-7) g(2) cm(-4) h(-1) of ex-situ TiC/hastelloy composites.
Titulo: Interfacial effect on oxidation resistance of TiC/hastelloy composites applied for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnects

Sentencas: Besides, smaller TiO2 area is formed on in-situ TiC/hastelloy composites with smaller interparticle spacing of TiC, against the prediction that the decrease of interparticle spacing of TiC accelerates the formation of continuous TiO2 area.
Titulo: Interfacial effect on oxidation resistance of TiC/hastelloy composites applied for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cell interconnects
